    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-10-20T13:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-10-20T13:00:00-05:00" n="666"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d666">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">832.5151/445: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-10-20T13:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 20, 1934—1 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>157. The Consulate General’s air mail despatch of October 5 entitled
                    Brazilian-German Exchange Arrangement,<note n="65" xml:id="d666fn65">Not
                        printed.</note> a copy of which appears to have been supplied to your
                    Embassy, implies that a Press statement by the Federal Foreign Trade Council,
                    apparently that enclosed with your No. 447 of the same date,<note n="65"
                        xml:id="d666fn66">Not printed.</note> is an admission that imports from
                    Germany receive exchange cover more promptly than those from the United
                    States.</p>
                <p>Please cable your comment.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
